text.paragraph:
In pediatric patients aged 2 to <4 years, treatment should also be initiated at a daily dose of 8-10 mg/kg generally not to exceed 600 mg/day, given in a BID regimen. For patients under 20 kg, a starting dose of 16-20 mg/kg may be considered (see 
                                    CLINICAL PHARMACOLOGY
                                 ). The maximum maintenance dose of oxcarbazepine should be achieved over 2-4 weeks and should not exceed 60 mg/kg/day in a BID regimen.
